Lewes to Newhaven Harbour Train Travel Guide

Travelling by train from Lewes to Newhaven Harbour provides passengers with a convenient and efficient way to commute or explore, ensuring that they arrive on time. For a smooth travel experience, please check out our Train Journey Planner.

Plan Your Train Journey

Travelling by train from Lewes to Newhaven Harbour takes approximately 11m. There is an average of 36 train from Lewes to Newhaven Harbour per day. The first train departs at 06:00, and the last train leaves at 23:32. For more detailed information, please consult our Train Journey Planner and Timetable.

Book Cheap Train Tickets

Train tickets from Lewes to Newhaven Harbour are available with Split Ticket and Advance tickets. The average fare is around £3.50, while the cheapest fare is £3.50*. Besides, you can book cheap tickets on off-peak time, which usually begin at 09:30.(Intercity Off-Peak times: Monday to Friday from 09:30 to 16:00, and after 19:00) . Accurate ticket prices vary depending on the time of day, route, and class selected.

Train Stations

You can choose to start from Brighton,Brighton,Fratton,Portsmouth,Clapham Junction,Clapham,London Victoria,or London Station to Newhaven Harbour by train.
